%% Diagram: Heartbeat + reclaim of a stalled worker
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant W as Worker
    participant DB as Tasks table
    participant J as Janitor / scheduler
    W->>DB: claim row 42 (status=running, last_heartbeat=t0)
    loop every 2-3 s while task running
        W->>DB: UPDATE tasks SET last_heartbeat=now() WHERE id=42
    end
    Note over W: Worker process crashes
    J->>DB: SELECT id WHERE status='running' AND last_heartbeat older than 30s
    DB-->>J: row 42
    J->>DB: UPDATE tasks SET status='pending', attempts=attempts+1, picked_by=NULL WHERE id=42
    Note over J,DB: Time-to-detect = interval × missed-beat threshold. Make detection window longer than worst-case GC pause to avoid false reclaims.
